            of managers, say project expectations and requirements are not set up front.

      .row.u-margin-bottom-lg
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-1
          %p Transparency lags behind for some teams, with a quarter of developers indicating they do not have visibility into what others, such as their colleagues in operations, product, and security, are working on. Remote or mostly remote teams lead their in-office counterparts in visibility into what others are working on, likely due to the fact that remote teammates need to be more deliberate about communication and planning in order to succeed.

          %p Although a strong majority feel comfortable proposing new ways of working, they face difficulty overcoming the status quo. Replacing ingrained practices, along with a resistance to change, are the top two challenges identified by all respondents.

      .row
